#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "A few years ago, anyone would have sold their own mother to be in my shoes. Now I'm ready to eat rotten canned food and drink water from a puddle. Now even I would prefer to be a worm in someone's ass than myself."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "After the explosion, the WSS is weaker than ever. There's no one left to prove anything to, but I want to find Davies, if he's still alive. If not, I'll shoot what's left of him, then build a new reactor on his snowy grave and blow it up again."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "All is lost..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "All the documentation was stored in the office next to the reactors. I'm sure there wasn't a single intact transistor from the hard drives, not a single intact molecule of paper... Future generations, if any survived, simply won't be able to catch up with this entire scientific base; they'll never have a single new reactor."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Am I personally to blame for the disaster? On the one hand, I have nothing to do with the reactors' operation. But on the other hand, my politics... Who cares now? Is there anyone here besides me?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Are you so carried away playing the King of Europa that you've decided to lay down your bones on it? I'll help you if you ask nicely."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "At the time of the disaster, my father was on the other side of the globe. They were exploring the possibility of building a second set of reactors on the opposite side, because they could evaporate water much more efficiently there than on the busy half of Europa. Is he still alive? If he understands what happened..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Come here!"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Damn it! Damn it!"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Did the mouse come into the cat's mouth on its own?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Even before the disaster, this so-called 'president of humanity' deserved to be deported to Earth to rot alive from radiation. Now he deserves to become breakfast for one of these creatures. I'm ready to lie down on the next plate just to see it with my own eyes."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Father! You're alive! I thought..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Father, what are you doing here? Lord, you're alive! But Mother..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Hey!"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "I can't believe my eyes! Why didn't you fly away, you idiot? Are you couldn't fit into the shuttle with a ton of other people's money?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "I met one of ours, but at that moment the ghoul was already sucking in his intestines like fucking spaghetti..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "I was chosen to rule Europa, and I'd rather freeze 100 meters into the ice than fly away from here. And where would I fly to? The world is ending. I choose to sink along with 'my ship.'"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "I was testing the ice strength on the uninhabited side of the satellite. As soon as I felt the jolt, I immediately realized what had happened. But what the hell? The reactors had been operating for almost 20 years without a single breakdown, without a single minute of downtime."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "I will never forget you 我的心肝"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "I'd served in the air force for over five years; if only there was even one surviving ship here... But where would I go? All the generation ships are already somewhere at the edge of the solar system, and a regular wreck could only get me to Io at best."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "I'll fix everything, I guess."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "I've killed a hundred people on Europa, two hundred on Earth, without flinching. But when I see these creatures, I want to hide in a corner like a child... What will happen to us now?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Idiots!"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Is anyone there?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "It's time to act"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:18
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Junior research fellow"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Members of the SSB, especially me, weren't welcome in respectable circles before. But now I feel like I'm being looked at askance even within the SSB itself. Maybe it's paranoia? I haven't slept for three days..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "My mother used to say that people like me, those born here, are something... Something that shouldn't have been. How did they get so far from home? Science drives progress, and the fear of being vaporized by a nuclear explosion pushes science at the speed of light."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "My parents remained on Earth and, like everyone else, perished in a nuclear war. I flew to Europa with the military, serving in the Canadian Army. There was no one to fight with in the peaceful, newly established Europa, so our unit was disbanded, and after wandering around, I ended up in the SSB, which became my second family."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "My parents spent almost their entire lives trying to develop a working tokamak. After their first major success, they were immediately recruited to Europa to build a terraforming center. A few years later, I was born. So, it turns out I'm as much of a native European as these monsters..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "My wife and I developed the first tokamak prototype, capable of producing hydrogen from water and triggering a nuclear fusion reaction. After successful tests and the launch of mass production, we were called upon to lead the terraforming of Europa. Work progressed rapidly until an explosion occurred, releasing enormous amounts of energy... My wife died immediately, but I managed to survive by a lucky coincidence.. Is our son alive?.."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Now I'm at the helm."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:18
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Nuclear physicist"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "People call me a terrorist, but my true goal is to overthrow the European regime and hand over power to those who deserve it. I am ready to sacrifice everything, including my life, to achieve this goal. If that means teaming up with underwater creatures, I'm in."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:17
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Phil McLee"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Phil? I'm glad you're alive, but what are you doing here? Where are the others?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:18
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Politician, head of the WCC"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Power will corrupt anyone. You can maintain control when you've gained power over hundreds, thousands, millions of people... But when you have the highest rank in the solar system... Is disaster the punishment for that? Now I'm an ordinary person and I'm as afraid as everyone else."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Sir, is that you? I thought I was the only one left! After the explosion, the military police from the WCC came running towards us. They started beating the crap out of the guys, I shot two and ran away without looking back. Where are we?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "So that's why it smelled like shit! The wind came before you. Even the spacesuit didn't help."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:18
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Space criminal, leader of the SSB"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:18
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Space criminal, retired soldier."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Stanislav once mentioned that after his death I would take his place. This information haunts me. I never wanted to take on such a burden before, but now I find myself terrified, thinking I'm ready to hasten his death to bring that moment closer."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "They say the explosion was so powerful that the ice on which the generators were standing melted 30 kilometers deep, and all that water instantly boiled. Not a single neuron in the heads of my mother and her colleagues even had time to move to realize what was about to happen to them..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "This isn't funny anymore, I can't believe we're standing here side by side."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "This time, hold the gun with both hands and try not to shake, sucker."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "We've been keeping a low profile most of the time, but now, after the disaster, it's time to act. Those idiots at the WCC, with their negligence, have done all the work for us; all we have to do is take matters into our own hands. All doors are open."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Well..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "What the hell are you doing here?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "What's going to happen to us now? We've dreamed of destroying the WSS our whole lives, but what do we do now? Do we have a plan?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Who is to blame?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Would all this have happened if the SSB terrorists had killed me that time? Just a couple of inches..."
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "You? Hahaha! Are you going to kill me? I'm doomed one way or another. Will you kill me or leave me for dessert for these ghouls?"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Zhang is that you? 你回来了真好! I felt like you survived!"
msgstr ""

#: lib/europa/server/characters.ex:0
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "这算怎么回事啊!"
msgstr ""
